SP  - 989
EP  - 1026
VL  - 71
IS  - 4
KW  - Common agency
KW  - balanced games
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1468-0262.00437
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We introduce a game of complete information with multiple principals and multiple common agents. Each agent makes a decision that can affect the payoffs of all principals. Each principal offers monetary transfers to each agent conditional on the action taken by the agent. We characterize pure-strategy equilibria and we provide conditions?in terms of game balancedness?for the existence of an equilibrium with an efficient outcome. Games played through agents display a type of strategic inefficiency that is absent when either there is a unique principal or there is a unique agent.
ER  - 

